@notice Checks if a group with the given public key is a stale group.
 Stale group is an expired group which is no longer performing any
 operations. It is important to understand that an expired group may
 still perform some operations for which it was selected when it was still
 active. We consider a group to be stale when it's expired and when its
 expiration time and potentially executed operation timeout are both in
 the past.

nodes.documentation:
@notice Reports unauthorized signing for the provided group. Must provide
 a valid signature of the group address as a message. Successful signature
 verification means the private key has been leaked and all group members
 should be punished by seizingtheir tokens. The submitter of this proof is
 rewarded with 5% of the total seized amount scaled by the reward adjustment
 parameter and the rest 95% is burned. Group has to be active or expired.
 Unauthorized signing cannot be reported for stale or terminated group.
 In case of reporting unauthorized signing for stale group,
 terminated group, or when the signature is inavlid, function reverts.
nodes.name: reportUnauthorizedSigning

 - 100% of the minimum stake after the first 6 months.

attributes.documentation:
@notice Checks if a group with the given public key is a stale group.
 Stale group is an expired group which is no longer performing any
 operations. It is important to understand that an expired group may
 still perform some operations for which it was selected when it was still
 active. We consider a group to be stale when it's expired and when its
 expiration time and potentially executed operation timeout are both in
 the past.

params.seed: Random number used as a group selection seed.

params.members: Group member addresses as outputted by the group selection protocol.
params.misbehaved: Bytes array of misbehaved (disqualified or inactive) group members indexes in ascending order; Indexes reflect positions of members in the group as outputted by the group selection protocol - member indexes start from 1.

expireOldGroups(Groups.Storage storage).notice: Goes through groups starting from the oldest one that is still active and checks if it hasn't expired. If so, updates the information about expired groups so that all expired groups are marked as such.

getGroupMembers(Groups.Storage storage,b.notice: Returns members of the given group by group public key.

getGroupMembers(Groups.Storage storage,u.notice: Returns addresses of all the members in the provided group.

hasWithdrawnRewards(Groups.Storage stora.notice: Return whether the given operator has withdrawn their rewards from the given group.

isStaleGroup(Groups.Storage storage,byte.notice: Checks if a group with the given public key is a stale group. Stale group is an expired group which is no longer performing any operations. It is important to understand that an expired group may still perform some operations for which it was selected when it was still active. We consider a group to be stale when it's expired and when its expiration time and potentially executed operation timeout are both in the past.

isStaleGroup(Groups.Storage storage,uint.notice: Checks if a group with the given index is a stale group. Stale group is an expired group which is no longer performing any operations. It is important to understand that an expired group may still perform some operations for which it was selected when it was still active. We consider a group to be stale when it's expired and when its expiration time and potentially executed operation timeout are both in the past.

relayEntryTimeoutPunishment(Groups.Stora.notice: Evaluates relay entry timeout punishment using the following rules: - 1% of the minimum stake for the first 3 months, - 50% of the minimum stake between the first 3 and 6 months, - 100% of the minimum stake after the first 6 months.

reportUnauthorizedSigning(Groups.Storage.notice: Reports unauthorized signing for the provided group. Must provide a valid signature of the group address as a message. Successful signature verification means the private key has been leaked and all group members should be punished by seizingtheir tokens. The submitter of this proof is rewarded with 5% of the total seized amount scaled by the reward adjustment parameter and the rest 95% is burned. Group has to be active or expired. Unauthorized signing cannot be reported for stale or terminated group. In case of reporting unauthorized signing for stale group, terminated group, or when the signature is inavlid, function reverts.

selectGroup(Groups.Storage storage,uint2.notice: Returns an index of a randomly selected active group. Terminated and expired groups are not considered as active. Before new group is selected, information about expired groups is updated. At least one active group needs to be present for this function to succeed.

setGroupMembers(Groups.Storage storage,b.notice: Sets addresses of members for the group with the given public key eliminating members at positions pointed by the misbehaved array.

terminateGroup(Groups.Storage storage,ui.notice: Terminates group with the provided index. Reverts if the group is already terminated.

withdrawFromGroup(Groups.Storage storage.notice: Withdraws accumulated group member rewards for operator using the provided group index. Once the accumulated reward is withdrawn from the selected group, the operator is flagged as withdrawn. Rewards can be withdrawn only from stale group.
